OL,3,CInfected blood victim 'upset' about
OL,4,C'relatively modest' compensation
OL,6,FLong-time infected blood scandal
OL,7,Fcampaigners "want to be more involved
OL,8,Fin the decisions that are being made
OL,9,Fabout them", an MP has warned.
OL,11,FLabour MP Clive Efford said his
OL,12,Fconstituent was "upset" at being
OL,13,Fpromised a #15,000 uplift to his
OL,14,Finfected blood compensation payment,
OL,15,Fbecause he attended Treloar's, a
OL,16,Ffigure which the Conservative shadow
OL,17,Fpaymaster general had earlier
OL,18,Fdescribed as "relatively modest".
